{"data":{"allFile":{"edges":[{"node":{"publicURL":"/static/ArgumentOverture.playground-0a82636146553297ec950ab0c2445ede.zip"}},{"node":{"publicURL":"/static/InferIt.playground-d2f2e8b847fff8540b15dc066466f2da.zip"}},{"node":{"publicURL":"/static/ReactifSwift.playground-3bd6c1b99908cf2a2deb4eb68f2720ee.zip"}},{"node":{"publicURL":"/static/Swifducks.playground-1573bc9d531c23af89ec12b8c4ee9802.zip"}}]},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>A Swift Playground aiming to provide some functional helpers to parse arguments for command line tools. It uses <a href=\"https://github.com/pointfreeco/swift-overture\">Overture</a> and is build for high composability, flexibility and little impact on your project's freedom to evolve.</p>\n<p>A central use case was <a href=\"https://github.com/vknabel/archery\">Archery</a>'s: only actually interpreted arguments shall be consumed. Any others shall be collected (<code class=\"language-text\">remaining</code>) or should prevent execution (<code class=\"language-text\">exhaust</code>), depending on the current command.</p>\n<p>First of all an example usage.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"swift\"><pre class=\"language-swift\"><code class=\"language-swift\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Experiment</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">do</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>isVerbose<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> whoToGreet<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> language<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">_</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">try</span> <span class=\"token function\">with</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"-v\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"hi\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Some string\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"--language\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token function\">chain</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n        <span class=\"token function\">flag</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"verbose\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"v\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token function\">positional</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Name\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token function\">argument</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"language\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"l\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        exhaust\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">catch</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Command failed:\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> error<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The implementation of the micro-library itself.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"swift\"><pre class=\"language-swift\"><code class=\"lan